<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911122-0142</DOCNO><DOCID>911122-0142.</DOCID><HL>   Ferruzzi Unit Signs China Pact</HL><DATE>11/22/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   I.FFI MNT</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)CONGLOMERATES (CGL)</MS><IN>CONGLOMERATES (CGL)CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)</IN><RE>CHINA (CH)EUROPE (EU)FAR EAST (FE)ITALY (ITA)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   BEIJING -- The giant Ferruzzi agro-industrial group ofItaly said its Montecatini Tecnologie unit and the BeijingResearch Institute of Chemical Industry signed a researchcooperation agreement.   They will collaborate on a series of research projects forthe development of chemicals, petrochemicals andintermediates, as well as in the field of &quot;environmentallyfriendly&quot; processes.</LP><TEXT>   Ferruzzi said it and Beijing Research will share theresearch costs and the ownership of the results. Exact termsweren't disclosed.   Montecatini, a part of the Montedison division ofcompanies within the Ferruzzi group, already has chemicalventures in China.</TEXT></DOC>